This paper deals with the development of an algorithm for estimating contact force and torque for vision-based tactile sensors, which is a common problem in the field of robotics (cs.RO). The algorithm is based on the observation of contact deformation patterns of hyperelastic materials, which involves computer vision techniques (cs.CV). The proposed method uses the Helmholtz-Hodge Decomposition (HHD) algorithm, which is a mathematical technique commonly used in machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG, cs.AI). Finally, the algorithm is integrated into a closed-loop adaptive grasp force control framework, which involves control systems and robotics (cs.SY).
